Test Summary: Stock based requisitions: Beginning balance from Stock on Hand

Test Data: Example values:  The period for which the requisition is initiated should be March 2018 if the physical inventory had been sent with the date of 28 February 2018
Expected Result: The requisition should be initiated.

Expected Result: The field should not be editable.

Test Summary: Stock based requisitions: Beginning balance from Stock on Hand
Step: Check whether the "Beginning balance" field contains correct values for all products.
Test Data: The value should be the same as had been in the "Current Stock" field when the physical inventory was conducted. If there were more lots of a given product in the inventory, the value should multiplied. E.g. if there were two lots and 100 was entered in the "Current Stock" field for all products, 200 should be visible in the "Beginning balance" field in the requisition.
Expected Result: The "Beginning balance" field should contain correct values for all products in the requisition.

Step: Click the "Submit & Authorize" button.
Expected Result: The requisition should be authorized.

Step: Check whether the "Beginning balance" field is editable for any of the products.

Step: Check whether the "Beginning balance" field contains correct values for all products.

Expected Result: The "Beginning balance" field should contain correct values for all products in the requisition.

Test Summary: 302 - View Stock Card by facility or program
Step: Log into OpenLMIS with user who can manage stock. Then go to Stock Management -> Stock on Hand.
Expected Result: User can see the Stock on Hand page.

Test Summary: 302 - View Stock Card by facility or program
Step: Ensure home facility is the facility selected, select a program and hit Search.
Expected Result: All stock cards for the program and facility are available in the table list.  NOTE: stock management for supervised facilities is not supported at this time.  Verify: - This list is paginated. - The list has the following columns: Product Code, Product, Lot Code, Expiry Date, Last Update, Stock on Hand and Actions. - If there are lots for a product, then the total Stock on Hand for the product must equal the sum of all lots.

Test Summary: 302 - View Stock Card by facility or program
Step: Select View next to a stock card.
Expected Result: User is directed to the Bin Card for the product.   Verify: - This view shows all the transactions for the product you have selected to view. - Sorted by date, with the most recent date at the top of the list. - This list is paginated. - The list has the following columns: Date, Receive from, Issue to, Reason, Adjustment, Stock on hand, Signature.

Test Summary: 302 - View Stock Card by facility or program
Step: Select Print button.
Expected Result: Printable page opens in new tab/window, that has the same information as the Bin Card screen.

Test Summary: 302 - View Stock Card by facility or program
Step: Select the back button in the browser.
Expected Result: User is back to the Stock on Hand screen.

Expected Result: User can see the Stock on Hand page.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: View Receiving Facility's CCE Status

Test Summary: Fulfillment: View Receiving Facility's CCE Status
Step: Verify the alert icon next to the status.
Expected Result: The alert icon should be inactive, an empty bell.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: View Receiving Facility's CCE Status
Step: Hover over the facility's CCE status.
Expected Result: A popover should show up, with the number of inventory items as the title, and each item on a row with the status, the reference name, and any alert icons. At least one should have an inactive alert icon, an empty bell, and none of them should be an active alert icon, a solid bell.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: View Receiving Facility's CCE Status

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Log into the application as vsrmanager1.
Expected Result: One should be logged in.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Initiate a requisition for the facility mentioned in the pre-conditions.
Expected Result: The requisition should be initiated.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Set the requested quantity for all products as 100.
Expected Result: The requested quantity for all not skipped products should be 100.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Submit and authorize the requisition.
Expected Result: The requisition should be authorized.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Log out and log in again as divo1.
Expected Result: One should be logged in.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Approve the above-mentioned requisition without any changes, so that Requested Quantity = Approved quantity.
Expected Result: The requisition should be approved and automatically converted to an order.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Go to Orders > Fulfill Orders and start fulfilling the above-mentioned order.
Expected Result: One should move to the "View Shipment" screen.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Order Quantity" column are expressed in packs.
Test Data: One has to divide the approved quantity by the product's net content (this can be viewed in the product's details on Administration > Products).   E.g. Approved Quantity in requisition = 100, net content for e.g. tetanus10 = 10 --> Order Quantity = 10
Expected Result: The values should be expressed in packs.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Insert any fill quantities not exceeding order quantities for given products.
Expected Result: The fill quantities have to be entered.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Click the "Generate Pick Pack list" button.
Expected Result: The pick pack list should open in a new tab.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Fill Quantity (doses)" and "Fill Quantity (vials)" are correct.
Test Data: Vials = Packs, so the value in the "Fill Quantity (vials)" column should be the same as on the "Fill Quantity" column on the "View Shipment" screen.  Dose = Pack * net content i.e. the value in the "Fill Quantity (doses)" column should equal to the number previously entered in the "Fill Quantity" column on the "View Shipment" screen multiplied by a given product's net content.
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Return to the "View Shipment" screen and confirm the shipment.
Expected Result: The shipment should be confirmed.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Go to Orders > View Orders and look for the above-mentioned order.
Expected Result: The order should be visible on the list.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Click the first button in the "Actions" column next to the order.
Expected Result: A PDF version of the order should open in a new tab.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether correct values are visible in the "Ordered Quantity" and "Dispensing Units" columns.
Test Data: "Ordered Quantity" = the same as in the "Order Quantity" column on the "View Shipments" screen.  "Dispensing Units" = Order quantity * the product's net content
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Return to the previous screen and click the second button in the "Actions" column next to the order.
Expected Result: A CSV file with the order's details should be downloaded.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Open the file and check whether correct values are visible in the "Ordered quantity" column.
Test Data: "Ordered quantity" = the same as in the "Order Quantity" column on the "View Shipments" screen or the same as in the "Ordered Quantity" column in the order's PDF version.
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Go to Orders > Manage Proof of Delivery.
Expected Result: The "Manage Proof of Delivery" screen should be displayed.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Look for the order for which the shipment had been previously confirmed and go to its details.
Expected Result: The screen with the PoD's details should be displayed.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Quantity Shipped" column are correct.
Test Data: "Quantity Shipped" = The same values as in the "Fill Quantity (vials)" column on the pick-pack list
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Step: Log out and log in again as divo1.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Approve the above-mentioned requisition without any changes, so that Requested Quantity = Approved quantity.
Expected Result: The requisition should be approved and automatically converted to an order.

Step: Go to Orders > Fulfill Orders and start fulfilling the above-mentioned order.
Expected Result: One should move to the "View Shipment" screen.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Order Quantity" column are expressed in packs.
Test Data: One has to divide the approved quantity by the product's net content (this can be viewed in the product's details on Administration > Products).   E.g. Approved Quantity in requisition = 100, net content for e.g. tetanus10 = 10 --> Order Quantity = 10
Expected Result: The values should be expressed in packs.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Insert any fill quantities not exceeding order quantities for given products.
Expected Result: The fill quantities have to be entered.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Click the "Generate Pick Pack list" button.
Expected Result: The pick pack list should open in a new tab.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Fill Quantity (doses)" and "Fill Quantity (vials)" are correct.
Test Data: Vials = Packs, so the value in the "Fill Quantity (vials)" column should be the same as on the "Fill Quantity" column on the "View Shipment" screen.  Dose = Pack * net content i.e. the value in the "Fill Quantity (doses)" column should equal to the number previously entered in the "Fill Quantity" column on the "View Shipment" screen multiplied by a given product's net content.
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Return to the "View Shipment" screen and confirm the shipment.
Expected Result: The shipment should be confirmed.

Expected Result: The order should be visible on the list.

Expected Result: A PDF version of the order should open in a new tab.

Test Data: "Ordered Quantity" = the same as in the "Order Quantity" column on the "View Shipments" screen.  "Dispensing Units" = Order quantity * the product's net content
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs

Expected Result: A CSV file with the order's details should be downloaded.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: Sort lots for fulfillment in recommended order
Step: Verify that the data within it follows order from acceptance criteria. Don't worry about how VVM status affects the sort order, though. That will be checked in later steps within this test.
Expected Result: Lots are sorted in recommended order:, nearest Expiry Date first, no date always goes first. Then, less Available SOH first.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: Sort lots for fulfillment in recommended order
Step: Navigate to "Stock Management" -> "Physical Inventory" and click Start for the EPI program  associated with D001 - Deposito Distrital Cuamba.
Expected Result: The " D001 - Depósito Distrital Cuamba - EPI" screen should be displayed.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: Sort lots for fulfillment in recommended order
Step: Fill in the data and click "Submit" button.
Test Data: Fill Current Stock same as SOH for every line except for MRK-ROTA-1-1234 ROTAM2017A which current stock should be changed to be lesser than MRK-ROTA-1-1234 ROTAM2017C. Assign ROTAM2017B VVM Status: Stage-2.
Expected Result: Physical inventory successful made.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: Sort lots for fulfillment in recommended order
Step: Go back to Shipment view by navigating to Orders -> Fulfill Orders and then clicking Continue Fulfillment next to the proper entry.  Check lines within orderable MRK-ROTA-1-1234.
Expected Result: Line with STAGE_2  	should be before STAGE_1 and no status, ROTAM2017A should be before ROTAM2017C as it has lesser Available SOH.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: Sort lots for fulfillment in recommended order
Step: Go to Stock Management  Adjustments and make not significant adjustment (so it's SOH still larger than ROTAM2017A) for Deposito Distrital Cuamba RotaTeq ROTAM2017C. Change VVM Status to STAGE_1.
Expected Result: Adjustment should be made.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: Sort lots for fulfillment in recommended order
Step: Go back to Shipment view by navigating to Orders -> Fulfill Orders and click "Continue Fulfillment" button.
Expected Result: The "View Shipment" screen should be displayed.

Test Summary: Fulfillment: Sort lots for fulfillment in recommended order
Step: Check lines within orderable MRK-ROTA-1-1234.
Expected Result: ROTAM2017A should be before ROTAM2017C as it has lesser Available SOH and STAGE_1/No VVM Status are treated as the same in sort order.

Expected Result: The requisition should be visible, and three buttons should be available at the bottom of the page: "Sync with server", "Reject" and  "Approve". In the product grid, there should be only two editable fields: "Approved quantity" and "Remarks". At the top of the page, the "Add Comment" button should be visible.

Test Summary: Requisitions: Approving and rejecting a requisition
Step: Add a comment that you are rejecting the requisition, and click the "Reject" button.
Expected Result: The comment should be saved, and the notification that the requisition had been rejected should appear. One should be redirected to the "Approve Requisitions" screen.

Test Summary: Requisitions: Approving and rejecting a requisition
Step: Log out and log in again as the Storeroom Manager, go to Requisitions > View and check the requisition's status.
Expected Result: The requisition's status should be "Rejected".

Test Summary: Requisitions: Approving and rejecting a requisition
Step: Click the "View Requisition" button next to the previously-rejected requisition.
Expected Result: The requisition should be visible. The comment on its rejection should be visible, and the data in the grid should be the same as when the requisition was being rejected. The user should be able to edit the requisition, and the "Submit" and "Delete" buttons should be available.

Test Summary: Requisitions: Approving and rejecting a requisition
Step: Enter new "Requested quantity" amounts and add a comment the you are resubmitting the rejected requisition with new totals.
Expected Result: The new data should be entered, the total requisition cost should update accordingly and the comment should be saved.

Test Summary: Requisitions: Approving and rejecting a requisition
Step: Submit the requisition.
Expected Result: The requisition should be submitted.

Test Summary: Requisitions: Approving and rejecting a requisition
Step: Log out and log in again as the Store Manager and go to the previously-submitted requisition. Check whether the previously-entered comment had been saved and whether the total requisition cost is up-to-date.
Expected Result: The comment should have been saved, and the total requisition cost should be as had been calculated when the new amounts were entered before the requisition's re-submission.

Step: Log into the application as vsrmanager1.
Expected Result: One should be logged in.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Initiate a requisition for the facility mentioned in the pre-conditions.
Expected Result: The requisition should be initiated.

Step: Set the requested quantity for all products as 100.
Expected Result: The requested quantity for all not skipped products should be 100.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Submit and authorize the requisition.
Expected Result: The requisition should be authorized.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Log out and log in again as divo1.
Expected Result: One should be logged in.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Approve the above-mentioned requisition without any changes, so that Requested Quantity = Approved quantity.
Expected Result: The requisition should be approved and automatically converted to an order.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Go to Orders > Fulfill Orders and start fulfilling the above-mentioned order.
Expected Result: One should move to the "View Shipment" screen.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Order Quantity" column are expressed in packs.
Test Data: One has to divide the approved quantity by the product's net content (this can be viewed in the product's details on Administration > Products).   E.g. Approved Quantity in requisition = 100, net content for e.g. tetanus10 = 10 --> Order Quantity = 10
Expected Result: The values should be expressed in packs.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Insert any fill quantities not exceeding order quantities for given products.
Expected Result: The fill quantities have to be entered.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Click the "Generate Pick Pack list" button.
Expected Result: The pick pack list should open in a new tab.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Fill Quantity (doses)" and "Fill Quantity (vials)" are correct.
Test Data: Vials = Packs, so the value in the "Fill Quantity (vials)" column should be the same as on the "Fill Quantity" column on the "View Shipment" screen.  Dose = Pack * net content i.e. the value in the "Fill Quantity (doses)" column should equal to the number previously entered in the "Fill Quantity" column on the "View Shipment" screen multiplied by a given product's net content.
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Return to the "View Shipment" screen and confirm the shipment.
Expected Result: The shipment should be confirmed.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Go to Orders > View Orders and look for the above-mentioned order.
Expected Result: The order should be visible on the list.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Click the first button in the "Actions" column next to the order.
Expected Result: A PDF version of the order should open in a new tab.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether correct values are visible in the "Ordered Quantity" and "Dispensing Units" columns.
Test Data: "Ordered Quantity" = the same as in the "Order Quantity" column on the "View Shipments" screen.  "Dispensing Units" = Order quantity * the product's net content
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Return to the previous screen and click the second button in the "Actions" column next to the order.
Expected Result: A CSV file with the order's details should be downloaded.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Open the file and check whether correct values are visible in the "Ordered quantity" column.
Test Data: "Ordered quantity" = the same as in the "Order Quantity" column on the "View Shipments" screen or the same as in the "Ordered Quantity" column in the order's PDF version.
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Go to Orders > Manage Proof of Delivery.
Expected Result: The "Manage Proof of Delivery" screen should be displayed.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Look for the order for which the shipment had been previously confirmed and go to its details.
Expected Result: The screen with the PoD's details should be displayed.

Test Summary: Order Quantity needs to be stored in Packs
Step: Check whether the values in the "Quantity Shipped" column are correct.
Test Data: "Quantity Shipped" = The same values as in the "Fill Quantity (vials)" column on the pick-pack list
Expected Result: The values should be correct.

Test Summary: Stock based requisitions: Beginning balance from Stock on Hand
Step: Check whether the "Beginning balance" field contains correct values for all products.

Test Summary: Requisitions: Requisition offline caching

Test Summary: Requisitions: Requisition offline caching
Step: Review the requisition totals and authorize it.
Expected Result: The requisition should be updated with the second requisition totals that had been completed in Firefox, as well as the comment entered in the former browser. The requisition should be authorized.
